  • Ulcer Index

A higher Ulcer Index value indicates greater downside risk and potential for larger drawdowns

  • Serenity Index

A higher Serenity Index generally indicates a fund with lower downside risk. This means the fund's returns are more consistent and less volatile, especially during market downturns.

  • Gain/Pain Ratio

A performance metric used to evaluate the profitability of a trading strategy. e.g., GPR of 2.33, suggests that for every dollar of loss, the trader gains $2.33 in profit.

  • Common Sense Ratio

A higher Common Sense Ratio suggests a more robust and potentially more profitable trading strategy. It indicates that the strategy not only generates profits but also has a tendency to produce larger winning trades while minimizing the impact of losing trades.

  • Outlier Win Ratio

A higher OWR suggests a strategy that produces a relatively high frequency of significantly large winning trades

  • Recovery Factor

A higher recovery factor indicates that the fund recovers from losses more rapidly. This is a desirable trait for investors, as it suggests resilience and the potential for stronger long-term performance.

  • Tail Ratio

A higher Tail Ratio suggests a strategy that produces a relatively high frequency of significantly large winning trades.
